Accounting software firm Sage has announced that it will be increasing prices for its Business Cloud products. The price increases will be effective from 1st October 2018, or the next renewal date thereafter. The base subscription will increase from R227 per month to R249 a month, with additional companies being charged at R233 per month, up from R212. These are the new prices: All prices are inclusive of VAT, Sage said. Read:Â Sage launches cloud-based accounting in South Africa